content:
You can now test and explore Data Cloud features in a sandbox org. The sandbox is a copy of your production org that you can use for testing, training, or creating customizations. When you create a sandbox, all your production org Data Cloud metadata and configurations are replicated in the sandbox. However, you canâ€™t deploy customizations or changes from a sandbox to production.

Where: This change applies to Data Cloud in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited editions. The production org must have a Data Cloud license.

NOTE Data Cloud in Sandbox is a pilot or beta service that is subject to the Beta Services Terms at Agreements - Salesforce.com or a written Unified Pilot Agreement if executed by Customer, and applicable terms in the Product Terms Directory. Use of this pilot or beta service is at the Customer's sole discretion. You can provide feedback and suggestions for the feature in the Trailblazer Community.

When: This functionality is available in July 2024.

How: In your production org, go to Feature Manager and opt in to Data Cloud in Sandbox. Create a sandbox using the UI or CLI. In the new sandbox, turn on Data Cloud in Data Cloud Setup.
